1. Init Containers are those containers that run before the main or app container for the particular work.
2. Init Containers motive for completion which means that the given work needs to be completed.
3. If a pod fails due to Init Containers then, Kubernetes restarts the init Container until it will succeed.


Use cases:
1. To install dependencies before running the application on main container.
2. clone a git repository into main volume
3. Generate configuration files dynamically
4. Database Configuration